  "computational_details": [],
  "unmapped_findings": [
    "800°C oxide map for Fe-Mn-Al system is divided into four regions based on scale morphology: Region I (alumina + bulky nodules), Region II (alumina + Mn-rich bulky oxides/threads), Region III (continuous protective alumina), Region IV (alumina + small Mn-rich nodules)",
    "Transition from Fe-rich to Mn-rich scales occurs at ~7.5 wt% Mn",
    "Austenite in duplex alloys is detrimental to oxidation resistance, promotes breakdown of pre-existing alumina scales and growth of bulky Mn-rich oxides",
    "Required Al concentration for protective alumina scale formation decreases with increasing oxidation temperature",
    "Mn vapor pressure induced void formation and nodule growth mechanism proposed for Region IV alloys (Al >9 wt%)",
    "Small Cr additions reduce required Al content for protective alumina scale formation without loss of oxidation resistance"
  ]
}